Labels
============
For the variable activity the following categories are given: 
1 WALKING
2 WALKING_UPSTAIRS
3 WALKING_DOWNSTAIRS
4 SITTING
5 STANDING
6 LAYING

Further data transformation
============
The data sets provided were correctly named and labeled to comply with “tidy” data sets. After the previous step, the “training” and the “test” data sets were merged in a new data set called “hartot”. 

As required in step 5 (Creates a second, independent tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject.), a tidy data set has been made taking only the mean for each subject and activity for the 69 variables. 
tidy <- ddply(hartot, .(subject, activity), summarize, 
              TimeDomainBodyAccelerationMeanXAxis=mean(TimeDomainBodyAccelerationMeanXAxis),
